    {
      "id": "PopularPost323481",
      "post_content": "Functionally, it counters counterspells (which in itself is pretty cool), and more often than not, target-spells will be fun to redirect to cause mayhem. Looking at you  [Oblivion Ring](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= Oblivion Ring ) ...  \n  \nOn the negatives, if it doesn't target, then its just a card with funny flavor text.  \n  \nBut considering the potential to steal enchantments and spells? Certain life-gain cards?  [Rancor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= Rancor )  ? Or your  [Murder](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= Murder )  ? Nice burn spell, think I'll take it...  \n  \nBlue playing spells that STEAL the opponent's strategy is as frightening as it gets.  \n  \nUpdate: This stole a  [Congregate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= Congregate )  from me. Considering there was a Selesnya and Zombie deck both playing in a group game...Lets just say, stealing 100+ life for 2 mana is pretty hilarious.",
      "posted_by": "DM3921",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost323481\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">Functionally, it counters counterspells (which in itself is pretty cool), and more often than not, target-spells will be fun to redirect to cause mayhem. Looking at you <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\" Oblivion Ring \" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= Oblivion Ring \"> Oblivion Ring </a>...<br/><br/>On the negatives, if it doesn't target, then its just a card with funny flavor text.<br/><br/>But considering the potential to steal enchantments and spells? Certain life-gain cards? <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\" Rancor \" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= Rancor \"> Rancor </a> ? Or your <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\" Murder \" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= Murder \"> Murder </a> ? Nice burn spell, think I'll take it...<br/><br/>Blue playing spells that STEAL the opponent's strategy is as frightening as it gets.<br/><br/>Update: This stole a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\" Congregate \" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name= Congregate \"> Congregate </a> from me. Considering there was a Selesnya and Zombie deck both playing in a group game...Lets just say, stealing 100+ life for 2 mana is pretty hilarious.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '323481'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n      